[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Java compilation issues**\n\nI'm wondering if running under the native image could be causing compilation problems, and I should avoid it unless necessary. The tests need to execute under native, but what if JavaCompiler isn't available? I could consider including source files or checking if test classes have module-info. Maybe there's a way to configure the build, but that feels too broad. Alternatively, could I use Instrumentation.appendToSystemClassLoaderSearch? However, it seems actual instrumentation isn't available. Maybe I could use JDK internal Unsafe to change the module field of the Installer class?\n\n**Considering runtime options**\n\nI need to avoid using runtime add-opens guards. Maybe I could try adding `runtimeArgs(\"--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED\")`? But I wonder if the native image runtime would accept that since the Java runtime already has `jvmArgs`. I suppose in `build.gradle`, all build arguments are included; perhaps I can add `--add-opens` in the native test runtime options? I’m not sure if the rules are flexible enough to allow that. Hm, more to think about!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c29c914fe4d860c0169f186471db4819fbf5bfabe180705bb\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8YZnQhAnKgcIqWZMA4AwBSJfDjDTWU8H_eqFg3uaxzESh74GqM3f-m4CU22tq2IlAYItWwcshl_Ugk8GW0YJ_0rJ4kxMEy9Yc_XivRLvG8fu8fGPRI-J80lIa8AeXKNJ3AYI9ne6rPlnLtO-syuGU4vRte2A-ljJaMX6c5hQCeYNKO_FlI0W03rMiR0E2I44Jj6ZXfBDKhJCjJ7bYz__1OzOIaNdJ3PB81Yg1gD5Ay9jc_3kI-oanf4MKgIGa1T_VLs3TKwgbnm-JkgPT5Lc2mUOtSc4oIjtkaMCmZGO-CFW0wiFRlj5bIg4u3ZGI0eOSEUr54zFPvrT6KQzvsjlMWOtjpfb6TkVdKIHEgqVpk-TUYm-umCCeLHyFR457C_jAQc9LrVDq6EoWIwuPcvcNcrDqTk8_LHOubDdrl46nUqO44eL18weo2_7OT_ZWySIEOMMPqc-3ppqpQpXz-qbpaC6OhZEUSc0UkCzXs2WiJw8KX85vUamE7Ixp8_nRE6tqsCLIBCgvmiO5qbpoGcMjCvSNB28eix_AyBAQd4OADCpCY6zlZyF-lyjGYu4GDLKYYwkc3mkJ5vIF9baB_AzTQ21WTVmHOiIAseOwngEO3zMQA